## Idea

If $k$ is a [[commutative ring]], $k$-linear (infinity,1)-categories are the analogue in [[(âˆž,1)-category]] theory of the notion of $k$-[[linear category]] in [[category theory]].

## Definition

A **$k$-linear (infinity,1)-category** is an [[additive (infinity,1)-category]] $A$ whose [[homotopy category of an (infinity,1)-category|homotopy category]] $ho(A)$ is a $k$-[[linear category]].

